ofiles modified by baryonic processes are therefore more consistent with\nexpectations from $\\Lambda$ cold dark matter ($\\Lambda$CDM) cosmology and\nprovide better fits to galaxy rotation curves across a wide range of galaxy\nproperties than do halo models that neglect baryonic physics. Our results offer\na solution to the decade long cusp-core discrepancy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 May 2016 14:24:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Jan 2017 15:21:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-18"}
